///How to test which ad performing better on Facebook?///////////////

To test which ad performs better on Facebook / Meta, use A/B Testing (Split Test) in Meta Ads Manager.

Step-by-step:
- Open Ads Manager
- Go to your campaign dashboard.
- Create a New Campaign

Choose your objective:
- Sales
- Leads
- Traffic
- Engagement
- App Promotion

Turn On A/B Test
During campaign creation, enable A/B Test.

Test One Variable at a Time
Example variables:
Creative → image vs video
Audience → male vs female / country vs country
Placement → Facebook Feed vs Instagram Feed
Headline/Text → different ad copy
CTA Button → Shop Now vs Learn More

Keep Everything Else Same
If testing image, keep:
same audience
same budget
same schedule
Set Budget & Run 3–7 Days

Example:
Ad A = $5/day
Ad B = $5/day

Check Results
Compare metrics like:
CTR (Click Through Rate)
CPC (Cost Per Click)
CPA (Cost Per Action/Lead/Sale)
ROAS (Return on Ad Spend)

Example:

Ad A:
Image ad
CTR 2.5%
CPC $0.10

Ad B:
Video ad
CTR 1.2%
CPC $0.25

→ Ad A is performing better.

Pro Tip:
- Duplicate one ad and change only one thing.
- This helps find the exact winning factor.

This process is called Creative Testing or Split Testing in digital marketing.


